title.narrative: HPN - Afya Halisi: Reproductive Maternal Newborn Child Health (RMNCH) National County

description.narrative: (Kenya): .Afya Halisi supports the journey to self-reliance in Kisumu, Kakamega, Migori, and Kitui counties by strengthening county systems and building local capacity for sustainable health outcomes in family planning, reproductive, maternal, newborn, child, adolescent health, and nutrition. Using FY 2019 funds, this activity builds county leadership, management, and governance skills through partnering with local organizations to expand community health programs and enhance public participation in county planning. Domestic resource mobilization efforts build skills for budgeting, planning, and policy-making to secure health funds. To support universal health coverage, the number of National Health Insurance Fund accredited health facilities is being increased and enrollment expanded among rural populations. This activity enhances the leadership role of the sub-county in health systems strengthening for integrated supply chain systems, enhancing the quality of the health information system, mentorship, and supportive supervision of health workers and service quality improvement. Specifically, service quality improvements focus on the provision of integrated family planning services, emergency obstetric and newborn care, antenatal care, intrapartum, and postnatal care for mother and newborn, prevention and case management of diarrhea and pneumonia, routine immunization, and promotion of infant and young child feeding. Social behavior change through local organizations will prioritize healthy timing and spacing of births, postnatal care for newborns, and broad social norm changes to prevent gender-based violence. At the national level, Afya Halisi helps to institutionalize annual inter-governmental performance reviews. Through its guidance, USAID efforts support the Kenya Integrated Country Strategy Goal three, and the State Department and USAID Joint Strategic Plan 2018-2022 objective of demonstrating U.S. values and leadership in global health...
